div.p:
"No"—said she slowly, and as if thinking to herself;
                                        "no—unless we took the Sinclair cottage for the
                                        summer."

"MR. Wheaton," said I, "we made a queer blunder the other night;
                                        we did not settle on any salary when we made out our call to
                                        Mr. Mapleson."

The baggage-master nodded thoughtfully. "So we ought," said he;
                                        and he added as he turned away, "I hope you're readier than
                                        I be."
